This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with object detection in images and videos. The use of weak supervision and incorporation of action labels also suggests that it could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The use of videos in the experiments could also make it relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) categories.
